{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4c7b1384-4bf5-4fb4-9b4c-0d275cc858f9","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Recursive wildcard glob (`**\\*.*`) — **High impact**\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nThe `**\\*.*` glob forces MSBuild to walk the **entire directory tree** during evaluation. This is the single most expensive evaluation pattern — cost grows with repository size and is re-paid on every evaluation (IDE reload, build, etc.).\n\n**Fix:** Scope the glob to specific extensions or directories actually needed.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `File.ReadAllText` property function — **Medium impact**\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nCalling `System.IO.File.ReadAllText` is **synchronous file I/O during evaluation**. Property functions run on every evaluation pass, not just at build time. This bypasses MSBuild's caching and item-tracking, causing unnecessary disk reads.\n\n**Fix:** If the content is only needed at build time, move it into a Target or use a task instead of an evaluation-time property function.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Chained 3-level import depth — **Low-medium impact**\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nEach `<Import>` adds a file-open + parse + evaluate cycle. Three deep-chained imports that each set a single property is unnecessary indirection. Deep import chains also make evaluation harder to debug with `/pp` or binlog.\n\n**Fix:** Flatten into a single `.props` file unless the layering serves a real modularity purpose.\n\n---\n\n### Summary (ordered by severity)\n\n| # | Pattern | Severity |\n|---|---------|----------|\n| 1 | `**\\*.*` recursive glob | 🔴 High |\n| 2 | `File.ReadAllText` in property | 🟡 Medium |\n| 3 | 3-level chained imports | 🟢 Low-Med |\n\nThe recursive glob is the dominant issue — in a large repo it can add **seconds** to every evaluation.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"348faba2-d956-4e55-b05f-4999fe8a89ce","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues.","outputTokens":565},"id":"c80fa2e7-abb9-4a45-9688-6321bc72961d","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:11:54.081Z","parentId":"dd4bfa2b-4ecf-4d17-b0c1-0bb4f2421caf"}
